[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a perfect hand for an opening bid of 2\C. 
23 points and balanced distribution is just fine.

SOUTH is glad to hear his partner has lots of points, because he was shortchanged. 
However, he must answer, so with 1 point he bids a negative 2\D.

NORTH describes her hand by saying 2NT. 
SOUTH does not have to bid the double negative over a 2NT bid, so he passes.}

